      "writtenOn": "2020-11-09T16:38:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, I was reading the spec a bit differently I think. Here\u0027s the spec on the \"result\" property:\n\n\u003e If supplied, then graphics that result from processing this filter primitive can be referenced by an ‘in’ attribute on a subsequent filter primitive within the same ‘filter’ element. If no value is provided, the output will only be available for re-use as the implicit input into the next filter primitive if that filter primitive provides no value for its ‘in’ attribute.\n\nAnd then separately the spec for the \"in\" property:\n\n\u003e If the value for ‘result’ appears multiple times within a given ‘filter’ element, then a reference to that result will use the closest preceding filter primitive with the given value for attribute ‘result’. Forward references to results are an error.\n\nTogether I was taking this to mean the filter DAG has some ordering (thus the std::vector and the reverse-search).",
      "parentUuid": "d1b51c6e_d62d55cc",
      "revId": "fcc955c8a3112d9b5e88e36c019d65ead6998538",
